sentences: Armstrong was the engineer on the 1997 Hokus Pick album Snappy.
Riley and his wife Shannon have one son, Zeffren, who was born in 2005.
During 2010 Riley Armstrong toured in the U.S. during which time he also opened for Starfield during their "The Saving One" tour.

A year later he released his own independent effort Novel Reason under the pseudonym Plain Edson.
He then moved from Vancouver to Nashville, where he spent the next five years.
Also that year Riley released the album La Loop on the 7 Spin Music indie label.
